### How to Download the GTZAN Genre Dataset

#### About the GTZAN Genre Dataset

The GTZAN Genre Dataset is a widely used benchmark dataset for music genre classification. It contains **10 different musical genres**, with **100 audio files per genre**, each lasting **30 seconds**. The genres included are:

* Blues
* Classical
* Country
* Disco
* Hiphop
* Jazz
* Metal
* Pop
* Reggae
* Rock

All audio files are **22050 Hz, Mono, 16-bit WAV files**. The tracks were collected between 2000 and 2001 from various sources, including personal CDs, radio broadcasts, and microphone recordings, to capture a wide range of recording conditions and styles.

---

#### Download from Marsyas

You can download the GTZAN Genre Dataset from the **Marsyas website**, which hosts datasets for music analysis, retrieval, and synthesis.

1. Go to the Marsyas dataset page: [Marsyas Datasets](http://marsyas.info/downloads/datasets.html)
2. Click **“Download the GTZAN genre collection”**. This will download a **.tar.gz** archive containing all the audio files.
3. Extract the archive using a tool like WinRAR, 7-Zip, or the built-in archive extractor in your operating system.
4. After extracting, you will see several file types. You can **discard all `.mf` files**, as they are not needed for genre classification.

---

#### Download from Kaggle

The dataset is also available on **Kaggle**, which may be easier if you already have a Kaggle account.

1. Visit the Kaggle dataset page: [GTZAN Dataset on Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/andradaolteanu/gtzan-dataset-music-genre-classification)
2. Click **Download** in the top-left corner.
3. In the downloaded archive, only the **`genres_original`** directory is required for your project; you can safely discard other files and directories.
4. **Important note:** One file, `jazz.00054.wav`, is known to be invalid. You need to delete this file and replace it with the correct version, which can be found here: [Correct Jazz File](https://www.kaggle.com/andradaolteanu/gtzan-dataset-music-genre-classification/discussion/158649)

---

This way, you’ll have the GTZAN Genre Dataset ready for music genre classification projects, with all necessary files properly prepared.
